21/02/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said on Sunday (February 20th) that he will resign as leader of his Justice and Development Party (AKP) if the party loses the general elections in June. At the same time, he expressed confidence that the AKP will win, saying the opposition has no targets or projects. "They [opposition parties] have already accepted defeat, and [are working] to find a reason for their defeat," Erdogan said. (Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, World Bulletin - 20/02/11)
